\[ad + ab + bc + 5c + 5d \le 5a + ab + bc + cd + 5d.\]This reduces to $cd - ad + 5a - 5c \ge 0,$ which factors as $(5 - d)(a - c) \ge 0.$  We know $5 - d \ge 0,$ so $a - c \ge 0.$  And since $a$ and $c$ are distinct, $a > c.$

